			<a href="mailto:rbarker@ucsd.edu">Celandro</a></font> 
			<font color="black">On:&nbsp;07/08/1999 1:18:27 PM</font></b></font>
	
		</td>
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				All goblins before the flag room are level 14-18. <BR>
After this things start getting harder.  There are<BR>
7 spawns in the flag room and 2 directly behind it<BR>
so be very careful when attempting to take out <BR>
this room.  To the left from the flag room is a <BR>
door which has some 17-21 goblins of various <BR>
types. There is a cave like entrance to even more <BR>
goblins but I have not explored there yet.  To <BR>
the right are some level 19-23 goblins and then a <BR>
gate.  There are 3 spawns at the gate usually <BR>
some combination of regular goblins, priests, and <BR>
evokers with an occasional prelate (never killed<BR>
him).  Behind the gate there is a large room to <BR>
the left behind another gate and then a cavernous <BR>
room straight ahead that has a very large number <BR>
of goblins 19-23 in it.  <BR>
<BR>
The goblin loot gets progressively better with <BR>
cloth, rawhide and ringmail armor as well as <BR>
bronze weapons being found from the entrance on <BR>
and the cash loot ranging from a gold or so to <BR>
over 2 plat sometimes for the high level evokers.<BR>
Mob control classes (bards and enchanters) are <BR>
highly recommended at the current low player <BR>
population as are large groups (preferably 6).<BR>
For higher level characters there are some very <BR>
good items that I wont name that come off some of<BR>
the higher leveled goblins such as the king. This <BR>
dungeon empties out around midnight PST and I have<BR>
been the only person in the zone.  When this <BR>
happens, the spawn rate drops to near nill with<BR>
only casters spawning rarely for melee types.<BR>
Very fun zone overall with good loot, exp, and <BR>
excitement.<BR>
Oh and if you ever see 30 goblins running by or a<BR>
wolf of any kind, get out fast. You'll thank me <BR>
later
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
